{
  "_comment": "ZLAR Canonicalization Parity Test Vectors (X1 / GATE-50-A). Each case is exercised through three implementations: IMPL-A jq -cS, IMPL-B lib/canonicalize.mjs canonicalize(), IMPL-C lib/human-invariants.mjs canonicalJSON(). The test asserts byte-identical output across all three on ZLAR-constrained input. Two tiers: Tier 1 = byte content (no trailing newline; spec form), Tier 2 = raw bytes (jq's trailing newline; bash-pipeline form). 'expected_oracle' (optional) is a hand-computed ORACLE-A reference; absent means ORACLE-B (jq as ground truth) only. 'strip_hmac:true' on a case routes the harness through the strip-then-canonicalize pipeline for HMAC parity. Floats / NaN / Infinity / non-ASCII keys are out of scope per IMPL-B contract.",
  "cases": [
    { "id": "P001", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Empty object",
      "input": {}, "expected_oracle": "{}" },
    { "id": "P002", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Empty array",
      "input": [], "expected_oracle": "[]" },
    { "id": "P003", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Null",
      "input": null, "expected_oracle": "null" },
    { "id": "P004", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Boolean true",
      "input": true, "expected_oracle": "true" },
    { "id": "P005", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Boolean false",
      "input": false, "expected_oracle": "false" },
    { "id": "P006", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Integer zero",
      "input": 0, "expected_oracle": "0" },
    { "id": "P007", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Integer one",
      "input": 1, "expected_oracle": "1" },
    { "id": "P008", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Integer negative one",
      "input": -1, "expected_oracle": "-1" },
    { "id": "P009", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Empty string",
      "input": "", "expected_oracle": "\"\"" },
    { "id": "P010", "category": "PRIM", "description": "ASCII string hello",
      "input": "hello", "expected_oracle": "\"hello\"" },
    { "id": "P011", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with backspace (\\b standard escape)",
      "input": "a\bb", "expected_oracle": "\"a\\bb\"" },
    { "id": "P012", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with newline",
      "input": "line1\nline2", "expected_oracle": "\"line1\\nline2\"" },
    { "id": "P013", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with tab",
      "input": "col1\tcol2", "expected_oracle": "\"col1\\tcol2\"" },
    { "id": "P014", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with form-feed",
      "input": "a\fb", "expected_oracle": "\"a\\fb\"" },
    { "id": "P015", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with carriage return",
      "input": "a\rb", "expected_oracle": "\"a\\rb\"" },
    { "id": "P016", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with embedded quotes and backslash",
      "input": "say \"hi\" and \\", "expected_oracle": "\"say \\\"hi\\\" and \\\\\"" },
    { "id": "P017", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with forward slash (R1: V8 and jq agree on no escape)",
      "input": "a/b/c", "expected_oracle": "\"a/b/c\"" },
    { "id": "P018", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with URL-like content (slash density)",
      "input": "https://zlar.ai/path", "expected_oracle": "\"https://zlar.ai/path\"" },
    { "id": "P019", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with control char 0x01 (\\u0001)",
      "input": "a\u0001b", "expected_oracle": "\"a\\u0001b\"" },
    { "id": "P020", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with control char 0x1F (\\u001f)",
      "input": "a\u001fb", "expected_oracle": "\"a\\u001fb\"" },
    { "id": "P021", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with DEL (0x7F; not a JSON control char — passed through)",
      "input": "ab", "expected_oracle": "\"ab\"",
      "accept_divergence": true,
      "divergence_reason": "jq -cS escapes U+007F as \\u007f (legacy-conservative; 10B output); V8 JSON.stringify passes raw 0x7F (RFC 8259-strict; 5B output). lib/canonicalize.mjs (IMPL-B) and lib/human-invariants.mjs canonicalJSON (IMPL-C) agree with V8/spec; jq is the outlier. Cross-gate signature gap on DEL-bearing payloads is latent but rare in practice (low probability per audit event; effectively zero for state schemas; receipts not exposed). Option 5b Phase 1 stopgap per ZLAR-Draft/build/x1-canonicalization-decision-memo-2026-05-11.md; Phase 2 MJS-to-jq normalization queued within 30 days. Full analysis: ZLAR-Draft/build/x1-divergence-findings-2026-05-11.md." },
    { "id": "P022", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Max safe integer 2^53-1",
      "input": 9007199254740991, "expected_oracle": "9007199254740991" },
    { "id": "P023", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Min safe integer -(2^53-1)",
      "input": -9007199254740991, "expected_oracle": "-9007199254740991" },
    { "id": "P024", "category": "PRIM", "description": "Unicode value (non-ASCII string value is allowed)",
      "input": "日本語", "expected_oracle": "\"日本語\"" },
    { "id": "P025", "category": "PRIM", "description": "String with all standard escapes packed together",
      "input": "\"\\\b\f\n\r\t", "expected_oracle": "\"\\\"\\\\\\b\\f\\n\\r\\t\"" },

    { "id": "K001", "category": "KEY", "description": "Two keys reverse alphabetical",
      "input": {"b": 2, "a": 1}, "expected_oracle": "{\"a\":1,\"b\":2}" },
    { "id": "K002", "category": "KEY", "description": "Three keys reverse alphabetical",
      "input": {"c": 3, "b": 2, "a": 1}, "expected_oracle": "{\"a\":1,\"b\":2,\"c\":3}" },
    { "id": "K003", "category": "KEY", "description": "Case-mixed keys (uppercase < lowercase by codepoint)",
      "input": {"b": 2, "A": 1, "a": 3}, "expected_oracle": "{\"A\":1,\"a\":3,\"b\":2}" },
    { "id": "K004", "category": "KEY", "description": "Digit-leading vs letter keys",
      "input": {"b": 2, "1": 1, "a": 3}, "expected_oracle": "{\"1\":1,\"a\":3,\"b\":2}" },
    { "id": "K005", "category": "KEY", "description": "Underscore sorts after uppercase, before lowercase",
      "input": {"_x": 1, "x": 2, "X": 3}, "expected_oracle": "{\"X\":3,\"_x\":1,\"x\":2}" },
    { "id": "K006", "category": "KEY", "description": "Hyphen (0x2D) sorts before underscore (0x5F)",
      "input": {"a-b": 1, "a_b": 2, "a": 3}, "expected_oracle": "{\"a\":3,\"a-b\":1,\"a_b\":2}" },
    { "id": "K007", "category": "KEY", "description": "Digits in key names use lexical not numerical order",
      "input": {"a10": 1, "a2": 2, "a": 3}, "expected_oracle": "{\"a\":3,\"a10\":1,\"a2\":2}" },
    { "id": "K008", "category": "KEY", "description": "Key containing forward slash",
      "input": {"b/c": 1, "a": 2}, "expected_oracle": "{\"a\":2,\"b/c\":1}" },
    { "id": "K009", "category": "KEY", "description": "Underscore-prefixed sorts after capital Z",
      "input": {"_private": 1, "Zpublic": 2, "apublic": 3}, "expected_oracle": "{\"Zpublic\":2,\"_private\":1,\"apublic\":3}" },
    { "id": "K010", "category": "KEY", "description": "Many keys (10) requiring full sort",
      "input": {"j": 10, "i": 9, "h": 8, "g": 7, "f": 6, "e": 5, "d": 4, "c": 3, "b": 2, "a": 1},
      "expected_oracle": "{\"a\":1,\"b\":2,\"c\":3,\"d\":4,\"e\":5,\"f\":6,\"g\":7,\"h\":8,\"i\":9,\"j\":10}" },

    { "id": "A001", "category": "ARRAY", "description": "Empty array",
      "input": [], "expected_oracle": "[]" },
    { "id": "A002", "category": "ARRAY", "description": "Single null",
      "input": [null], "expected_oracle": "[null]" },
    { "id": "A003", "category": "ARRAY", "description": "Three integers in order",
      "input": [1, 2, 3], "expected_oracle": "[1,2,3]" },
    { "id": "A004", "category": "ARRAY", "description": "Three strings in order (preserved, not sorted)",
      "input": ["c", "a", "b"], "expected_oracle": "[\"c\",\"a\",\"b\"]" },
    { "id": "A005", "category": "ARRAY", "description": "Nested arrays",
      "input": [[1, 2], [3, 4]], "expected_oracle": "[[1,2],[3,4]]" },
    { "id": "A006", "category": "ARRAY", "description": "Mixed types",
      "input": [null, true, 1, "x", [], {}], "expected_oracle": "[null,true,1,\"x\",[],{}]" },
    { "id": "A007", "category": "ARRAY", "description": "Array of objects, each requiring key sort, array order preserved",
      "input": [{"z": 1, "a": 2}, {"m": 3, "b": 4}],
      "expected_oracle": "[{\"a\":2,\"z\":1},{\"b\":4,\"m\":3}]" },
    { "id": "A008", "category": "ARRAY", "description": "Array of nulls",
      "input": [null, null, null], "expected_oracle": "[null,null,null]" },

    { "id": "N001", "category": "NEST", "description": "Two-level nesting with sort at every level",
      "input": {"z": {"b": 2, "a": 1}, "a": {"d": 4, "c": 3}},
      "expected_oracle": "{\"a\":{\"c\":3,\"d\":4},\"z\":{\"a\":1,\"b\":2}}" },
    { "id": "N002", "category": "NEST", "description": "Three-level nesting",
      "input": {"outer": {"inner": {"deep": 1}}},
      "expected_oracle": "{\"outer\":{\"inner\":{\"deep\":1}}}" },
    { "id": "N003", "category": "NEST", "description": "Four-level with mixed types",
      "input": {"c": {"f": {"i": 9, "h": 8}, "e": 5}, "a": {"d": [3, 2, 1], "b": null}},
      "expected_oracle": "{\"a\":{\"b\":null,\"d\":[3,2,1]},\"c\":{\"e\":5,\"f\":{\"h\":8,\"i\":9}}}" },
    { "id": "N004", "category": "NEST", "description": "Empty nested structures",
      "input": {"a": {}, "b": [], "c": ""},
      "expected_oracle": "{\"a\":{},\"b\":[],\"c\":\"\"}" },
    { "id": "N005", "category": "NEST", "description": "Array of objects with nested arrays",
      "input": [{"k": [1, 2, {"x": "y"}]}, {"k": []}] },
    { "id": "N006", "category": "NEST", "description": "Deep recursion (5 levels)",
      "input": {"a": {"b": {"c": {"d": {"e": 1}}}}},
      "expected_oracle": "{\"a\":{\"b\":{\"c\":{\"d\":{\"e\":1}}}}}" },

